  "prompt": "What are the top 5 headphones under Rs.1000 in India?",
  "response": "Okay, finding truly *amazing* headphones under Rs. 1000 can be tricky.  You're often sacrificing sound quality or build quality at that price point. However, here are 5 options that consistently get decent reviews and offer a good balance of features and performance for the price in the Indian market, along with some important considerations:\n\n**Important Considerations Before You Buy:**\n\n*   **Sound Quality Expectations:** Be realistic. Don't expect audiophile-grade sound. You'll likely find a focus on bass response.\n*   **Durability:**  Cheaper headphones often break easily. Read reviews about durability and handle them with care.\n*   **Comfort:** Pay attention to ear cup size and padding, especially if you plan to wear them for extended periods.\n*   **Warranty:** Check for a warranty. Even a limited warranty is better than none.\n*   **Wired vs. Wireless:** At this price point, wired headphones generally offer better sound quality for the money. Bluetooth options might compromise on sound.\n\n**Top 5 Headphones Under Rs. 1000 (In no particular order):**\n\n1.  **boAt Bassheads 100/225/242:** These are ubiquitous in India and popular for their bass-heavy sound signature. They're generally in-ear earphones (earbuds).  Choose the model based on current availability and slight feature differences.  They're known for being affordable and readily available. The Bassheads 225, in particular, is often cited as a good budget choice.\n    *   **Pros:** Bass-heavy, widely available, very affordable, decent noise isolation for the price.\n    *   **Cons:** Sound quality not nuanced, can be fatiguing for long listening, durability can be a concern.\n\n2.  **realme Buds Classic:** Realme is becoming a strong contender in the audio space. The Buds Classic offer a decent sound signature with a good balance of bass and clarity for the price.\n    *   **Pros:** Good balance in sound, comfortable fit, decent build quality for the price.\n    *   **Cons:** Not as bass-heavy as some other options, cable quality might be a concern for some.\n\n3.  **JBL C50HI:** JBL is a reputable brand. The C50HI is a basic in-ear headphone that offers a relatively balanced sound signature compared to some of the bass-boosted options.\n    *   **Pros:** Decent sound quality for the price, reputable brand, comfortable fit.\n    *   **Cons:**  Might lack bass for some users, build quality is basic.\n\n4.  **Philips SHE1505BK/94:** Philips is a well-known brand, and this model delivers a decent sound at an affordable price point. It is an in-ear design.\n    *   **Pros:** Well-known brand, reliable build quality for the price.\n    *   **Cons:** Sound quality is pretty average compared to its competitors.\n\n5.  **Boult Audio Bass Buds Q2:** If you prefer a neckband Bluetooth earphone, this one often comes around within the budget.\n    *   **Pros:** Wireless, comfortable neckband design, good battery life.\n    *   **Cons:** Sound Quality can be middling, Bluetooth connectivity issues.\n\n**Important Notes and Alternatives:**\n\n*   **Monitor Availability:** Prices and availability fluctuate. Check online retailers like Amazon, Flipkart, and local electronics stores for the best deals.\n*   **Read Reviews:** Before buying, read recent customer reviews on the retailer's website. This will give you a better sense of real-world performance and durability.\n*   **Consider Refurbished/Used:**  Sometimes you can find slightly better quality headphones (that were originally more expensive) in the refurbished or used market within your budget.  Buy from reputable sellers with return policies.\n*   **Increase Your Budget (if possible):** If you can stretch your budget even by a few hundred rupees, you'll find noticeably better quality options.\n\n**Final Recommendation:**\n\nFor wired in-ear headphones, I'd recommend starting with the **realme Buds Classic** or **JBL C50HI** based on your preference for bass. The **boAt Bassheads** are a solid choice if you are looking for something that is really cheap.  If you *must* have wireless, research the reviews on the specific **Boult Audio** model available within your budget carefully, as Bluetooth performance and sound quality can vary significantly in this price range.  Always prioritize reading recent customer reviews before making a purchase!\n",
